Looking at this, I've traced every variable in `solution.ex` and confirmed the pure logic is clean. The most plausible source of a lingering compile warning is the loosely-typed value access in `summarize/1`: `result` is pulled out of the `Task.async_stream` comprehension (whose element type is only `{:ok, term()} | {:exit, term()}`), and then `result.matched`/`length(result.matched)` blindly access map fields on a value the compiler can't prove is a map. I'll fix that by explicitly destructuring the well-known shape in the reducer, which silences the warning and is behavior-identical (`do_reconcile/4` always returns exactly that shape).

